# 24. Deployment Verification and Troubleshooting

> This section documents the actual issues encountered during the deployment of Wazuh on an Apple Silicon M5 system using OrbStack and Docker. Each issue includes the symptoms, root cause, diagnostic process, resolution, and lessons learned.

---

# Issue 1 – Wazuh Docker Image Not Found

## Symptom

During the initial deployment, Docker failed to download the specified image.

Command:

```bash
docker compose pull
```

Observed Error:

```text
Error response from daemon:
failed to resolve reference
docker.io/wazuh/wazuh-manager:5.1.0

not found
```

---

## Root Cause

The Docker Compose file referenced:

```yaml
image: wazuh/wazuh-manager:5.1.0
```

At the time of deployment, that image tag was not available from the Docker registry.

This caused Docker to stop before creating any containers.

---

## Investigation

Verify the image tag referenced in:

```text
docker-compose.yml
```

Compare it with the version available in the Wazuh repository documentation.

---

## Resolution

Instead of continuing with the unavailable image tag, the deployment switched to the stable **4.14.6** release.

After updating the deployment files, Docker successfully downloaded:

* wazuh-manager:4.14.6
* wazuh-indexer:4.14.6
* wazuh-dashboard:4.14.6

---

## Lesson Learned

Always verify Docker image tags before deployment.

Do not assume the newest version is immediately available for every deployment method.

