# Issue 3 – YAML Validation Errors

## Symptom

Docker Compose refused to start.

Validation Errors Included:

```text
additional properties 'external', 'name'
not allowed
```

and

```text
found a tab character
that violates indentation
```

---

## Root Cause

The Compose file had been modified incorrectly.

Problems included:

* Invalid network syntax
* Incorrect indentation
* Tab characters instead of spaces

YAML is indentation-sensitive.

One misplaced tab can invalidate the entire file.

---

## Resolution

The file was edited using VS Code.

Indentation was converted to spaces.

Network configuration was corrected.

Docker Compose validation succeeded.

---

## Lesson Learned

Always use a YAML-aware editor.

Never mix tabs and spaces.

