# Lessons Learned

The deployment reinforced several engineering principles:

1. Verify image versions before deployment.
2. Confirm repository contents before running commands.
3. YAML syntax errors can prevent deployment before containers are created.
4. TLS certificate paths must reference files, not directories.
5. Use container logs before attempting reinstallation.
6. Investigate the root cause rather than repeatedly restarting services.
7. Validate the deployment after every major change.
8. Document every issue and its resolution for future reference.

